    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hi, I propose to add an option (by default not enabled) to hide the binary size warnings that are in general useful but can easily give false alarms. Examples:\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/432\r\n- https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/5343\r\n- https://morepypy.blogspot.ca/2018/04/how-to-ignore-annoying-cython-warnings.html\r\n\r\nThe second link is an example of NumPy devs considering not merging a clear improvement because of this warning, and the third one of PyPy devs publishing a complete package just to install a warning filter to work around the false alarm. \r\n\r\nWhen package authors know that it's going to be a user-visible false alarm (and it's quite an alarming/confusing one for users), then giving them an option to do a release with the check disabled seems quite valuable.\r\n\r\n",
